cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.AR 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for implementing back propagation on discrete deep neural networks. It also involves training deep neural networks with ternary weights and activations, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in image recognition and event-driven hardware design. The paper may also be relevant to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.AR (Augmented Reality) as it involves developing more efficient and flexible deep neural networks for various hardware platforms.
